##CAD-12 Q2 Write a program that asks the user to enter a word and determines whether the word is a palindrome or not.
## A palindrome is a word that reads the same backwards as forwards
userinput=input('enter the string: ')
if(userinput==userinput[:: - 1]):
     print("it is a palindrome")
else:
      print("it is not a palindrome")

 ## CAD-12 Q3: write a program that asks the user to enter a string, then print out each letter of the string doubled and on a seprate line.
 ##for instance, if the user entered HEY, the ouput would be
 ##hh
 ##ee
 ##yy

userinput = input("enter a string: ")
for i in range(len( userinput)):
     print(userinput[i]*2)'''

## CAD-12 Q4:##Write a program that asks the user for a large integer and inserts commas into it according to the standard American convention for commas in large numbers.
##For instance, if the user enters 1000000, the output should be 1,000,000.( Try for India format 10,00000)
number=input("enter a large integer: ")
b= {number}.format(",")
print(b)
